# ARIA2C
Nixpkgs: nixpkgs.aria2
Source: https://github.com/aria2/aria2
Description: Lightweight multi-protocol & multi-source command-line download utility.
Version: aria2c --version

## Commands

### Basics
- aria2c <url>: Download a single file.

### Essentials
- aria2c -x 16 -s 16 <url>: Download using 16 connections and 16 splits.
- aria2c -i list.txt: Download multiple URLs from a file.

### Intermediaries
- aria2c --continue=true <url>: Resume a partial download.
- aria2c --max-download-limit=1M <url>: Cap download speed.

### Advanceds
- aria2c --enable-rpc: Start aria2 as an RPC server for remote control.

### Uncommons
- aria2c "magnet:?xt=urn:btih:..." : Download via BitTorrent magnet link.

## Tips
- Use --daemon to run the download in the background.

## Disclaimers
- Concurrent connections may be blocked by some servers (Rate Limiting).

## Alternatives
- wget: Simpler, single-threaded.
- curl -O: Standard tool for quick downloads.

